# 🟢 Simple Network Configuration Lab

This is a basic Cisco Packet Tracer home lab demonstrating foundational networking concepts.

## 🔧 Objectives

- Configure basic Router and Switch settings
- Establish PC-to-PC communication (ping)
- Implement basic IP addressing (no subnetting)

## 🖥️ Devices Used

- 2x PCs
- 1x Switch
- 1x Router

## ✅ Lab Goals

- Verify successful connectivity between hosts
- Test basic network functionality
- Gain familiarity with Packet Tracer and CLI commands

---

### Notes:
- The `.pkt` file is included.
- Screenshots and configuration files are added for clarity.
